Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Azerbaijan. The Azerbaijani Government has introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus.
Options for leaving Azerbaijan are becoming increasingly limited and if you wish to leave Azerbaijan you should make arrangements to do so as soon as possible.
Quarantine
The Azerbaijani authorities have informed that as of 21 March all nationals arrivals from abroad will be placed in to quarantine and that the Olympic Village in Baku will be used for the quarantining of British nationals. The quarantine period will be a minimum of 7 days. The British Embassy has been informed that if the quarantined individual gives two negative COVID-19 tests, they will be released on condition they self-quarantine for at least another 7 days. Similar procedures are also in place for British nationals who show signs of potential COVID-19 infection while staying in Azerbaijan.
If you or a British national you know is quarantined, contact the British Embassy immediately. Call: +994 12 437 7878 or you can reach us via Facebook.
Visas
The Azerbaijani authorities have introduced additional visa measures for British nationals. See Visas
Further information
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
